meta {
  name: GET /threads/{id}/stream — DAG-wide SSE
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/threads/{{root_request_id}}/stream
  body: none
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Accept: text/event-stream
}

docs {
  Live fan-in stream for every chunk emitted on any `prompt_requests` row
  in the DAG rooted at `{root_request_id}`. The handler subscribes a
  single broadcast receiver and forwards `text`, `reasoning`, `tool_call`,
  `tool_result`, `agent_message`, `done`, `error`, and `stalled` events
  with a per-connection monotonic SSE `id:` cursor.

  Per-event JSON envelope:
  ```
  {
    "request_id":  "<uuid|null>",
    "from_agent":  "<uuid|null>",
    "chunk_seq":   <bigint|null>,
    "chunk":       <ResponseChunk JSONB>
  }
  ```
  `request_id` / `from_agent` / `chunk_seq` are `null` only on synthetic
  `stalled` / `error` frames.

  The connection closes on the first terminal `done` chunk emitted when
  the DAG reaches quiescence. There is **no** Last-Event-ID resume — the
  per-thread cursor is in-memory and lossy on process restart by design.
  On reconnect, refetch `GET /threads/{id}/messages` and dedupe by
  `(request_id, chunk_seq)`.

  Run "Prompts / Submit Prompt" first (or "Scenarios / Multi-Agent
  Scenario") so `root_request_id` is set in the env.
}
